[1]
Date: Wed 30 Nov 2011
From: Prof Norman Noah <Norman.Noah@lshtm.ac.uk> [edited]


It would be useful to know, from this sad story, what proportion of
children infected had clinical hepatitis; was it higher than 20
percent? If it was the same low rate as quoted [which includes
adults], there will be very many more children affected [theoretically
280].

Hopefully, all those who visited the clinic will be tested, and if
those who were injected with the same needle can be identified, it
should be possible to calculate the ratio of symptomatic to total
infected.

--
Professor Norman Noah MB; FRCP; FFPH
Professor of Public Health
Infectious Disease Epidemiology Unit
Dept of Epidemiology and Population Health
